{"search_data": "MeghalayaMegha Health Insurance Scheme (MHIS IV) Approved in Convergence with PMRSSMPradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (PMJAY)  \u2013 Complete DetailsAll the families in the Meghalaya state would now be covered under this MHIS 4th phase. So, govt. might not invite fresh enrollment for this phase of Megha Health Insurance Scheme.Megha Health Insurance Scheme (MHIS IV) in MeghalayaThe important features and highlights of MHIS 4th phase are as follows:-Meghalaya Health Insurance Scheme (MHIS), originally launched in December 2012, is all set to enter the 4th phase.This 4th phase will be launched in convergence with Ayushman Bharat Yojana \u2013 PMRSSMMHIS is a Universal Health Insurance Scheme to provide health insurance to all persons that are resident of the state.Insurance coverage under MHIS is increased to Rs. 5 lakh from previous Rs. 2.8 lakh. Now the insurance amount is Rs. 5 lakh per family per year for secondary and tertiary hospitalisation,However, state govt. and central govt. employees are excluded from this scheme.Meghalaya govt. has launched this scheme in the FY 2012 to provide financial assistance to all the citizens at the time of hospitalisation and reduce out-of-pocket expenses of residents.Till date, more claims worth Rs. 70 crore has already been given under MHIS III with more than 1 lakh patients taking advantage of medical treatment.It is important to note that, 100% hospitals in the state are now included in MHIS Scheme.List of empaneled hospitals, claim status, package rates and more information about the Megha Health Insurance Scheme can be found on the official website at http://mhis.nic.in  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}